      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(codex): format skills using Codex skills response shape",
        "body": "Before\n<img width=\"2394\" height=\"1864\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-05-27 at 14 32 24\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d1149ec1-b70c-4496-9ca8-e3bb93a8935e\" />\n\nAfter\n<img width=\"2362\" height=\"1832\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-05-27 at 14 49 40\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a3a0f585-ca73-40e1-bdad-3af134935cfc\" />\n\n## Summary\n\n- Format `/codex skills` with a skill-aware renderer instead of the generic list formatter.\n- Type `skills/list` to match Codex's current schema: `data[]` workspace groups containing `cwd`, `skills[]`, and `errors[]`.\n- Render `/codex skills` as a compact untruncated bullet list containing only code-styled enabled skill names.\n- Count nested enabled skills in `/codex status` instead of counting workspace groups.\n- Normalize each workspace and skill independently so one malformed skill entry does not derail the whole `/codex skills` response.\n- Keep the existing chat-display escaping so mentions and markdown-like text are still neutralized.\n- Report a sanitized load-error count when Codex returns only failed skill groups.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check -- extensions/codex/src/app-server/protocol.ts extensions/codex/src/command-formatters.ts extensions/codex/src/command-handlers.ts extensions/codex/src/commands.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/commands.test.ts`",
